WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.173 --> 00:00:09.241
<i>[Man Narrating] Hunger.
the poet once said.</i>

2
00:00:09.310 --> 00:00:11.776
<i>is the most important
thing we know.</i>

3
00:00:11.845 --> 00:00:14.679
<i>the first lesson we learn.</i>

4
00:00:14.748 --> 00:00:20.152
<i>But hunger can be easily
quieted down. easily satiated.</i>

5
00:00:21.389 --> 00:00:25.457
<i>There is another force.
a different type of hunger.</i>

6
00:00:25.526 --> 00:00:29.528
<i>an unquenchable thirst
that cannot be extinguished.</i>

7
00:00:29.596 --> 00:00:32.797
<i>Its very existence
is what defines us.</i>

8
00:00:32.866 --> 00:00:36.001
<i>what makes us human.</i>

9
00:00:36.070 --> 00:00:38.336
<i>That force is love.</i>

10
00:00:40.874 --> 00:00:43.608
Uh. folks. this is your
captain up in the flight deck.

11
00:00:43.677 --> 00:00:47.179
We are on our final descent into
New York for an on-time arrival.

12
00:00:48.265 --> 00:00:49.998
We want to thank you
for flying Regis Air...

13
00:00:50.066 --> 00:00:51.583
and encourage that you ask us...

14
00:00:51.652 --> 00:00:54.436
<i>any connecting gate
information you may need.</i>

15
00:00:54.505 --> 00:00:56.354
<i>We're looking at
partly cloudy skies...</i>

16
00:00:56.423 --> 00:00:58.501
<i>and may hit a little turbulence
on our approach...</i> [Phone Ringing]

17
00:00:58.525 --> 00:01:01.193
<i>so make sure those seat
belts are fastened.</i> Not again.

18
00:01:04.164 --> 00:01:06.664
Yes? <i>[Man] Rose.
get back here! Now!</i>

19
00:01:06.733 --> 00:01:08.032
<i>I need your help!</i>

20
00:01:08.102 --> 00:01:11.303
We're landing. Whatever it
is can wait. <i>Now! Come now!</i>

21
00:01:12.072 --> 00:01:13.638
All right. relax.

22
00:01:18.112 --> 00:01:21.579
<i>♪♪ [Headset: Rock]</i>
Sir? We're landing.

23
00:01:21.648 --> 00:01:24.193
- Would you power off
your device?
- You call this a device?

24
00:01:24.217 --> 00:01:25.750
You have to turn it off.

25
00:01:25.819 --> 00:01:29.071
It's like when a cop
calls a car a "vehicle"...

26
00:01:29.139 --> 00:01:33.141
or. uh. when he calls you
"sir" when he means "asshole."

27
00:01:33.210 --> 00:01:36.210
Having a little gig in
New York coming up.

28
00:01:36.279 --> 00:01:39.648
You give me three or four of those little
baby vodkas. I'll get you a front-row seat.

29
00:01:40.834 --> 00:01:42.362
Turn it off. Put your seat up.

30
00:01:42.386 --> 00:01:44.770
We're landing.<i> sir.</i>

31
00:01:47.491 --> 00:01:49.657
Ma'am.

32
00:01:51.228 --> 00:01:53.290
- Seat backs
in the upright position.
- Finally.

33
00:01:53.314 --> 00:01:56.231
<i>[Tone Chimes] [Captain] Flight
attendants. prepare for landing.</i>

34
00:01:56.299 --> 00:01:59.017
- [Girl Speaking French]
- [French]

35
00:02:07.728 --> 00:02:09.761
<i>♪♪ [Earphones: Pop]</i>

36
00:02:12.716 --> 00:02:14.710
<i>[Tone Chimes] [Captain]
On behalf of the cabin crew.</i>

37
00:02:14.734 --> 00:02:18.153
<i>I want to say that we know you have
many choices when it comes to air travel...</i>

38
00:02:18.222 --> 00:02:20.889
Peter. You haven't done anything
back here! This place is a mess!

39
00:02:20.958 --> 00:02:22.936
There's something in the
plane. What do you mean?

40
00:02:22.960 --> 00:02:25.638
Inside the plane! Something
alive in the cargo hold!

41
00:02:25.662 --> 00:02:27.195
<i>[Tone Chimes]</i>

42
00:02:27.264 --> 00:02:28.904
<i>We'd like to extend
a special thank you...</i>

43
00:02:28.948 --> 00:02:32.083
<i>to any Black Platinum Award
members flying with us tonight...</i>

44
00:02:32.152 --> 00:02:33.701
<i>and encourage all
our passengers to...</i>

45
00:02:33.770 --> 00:02:35.954
What the hell do you
mean? Like a dog?

46
00:02:36.022 --> 00:02:38.134
No. Something
really. really big.

47
00:02:38.158 --> 00:02:39.991
I heard it move.

48
00:02:40.060 --> 00:02:42.572
A thumping underneath
the floor. I heard it trying...

49
00:02:42.596 --> 00:02:45.013
No. Peter. There are no
animals on the manifest.

50
00:02:45.082 --> 00:02:49.635
It tried to open the latch. I heard
a noise. Then it moved away.

51
00:02:49.703 --> 00:02:51.703
But you can feel it moving.

52
00:02:52.956 --> 00:02:56.008
<i>[Tone Chimes] Flight
crew. prepare for arrival.</i>

53
00:02:58.145 --> 00:03:01.914
[Slow. Deliberate Breathing]

54
00:03:05.185 --> 00:03:08.186
[Creaking] [Breathing Continues]

55
00:03:09.990 --> 00:03:12.991
[Whirring]

56
00:03:14.244 --> 00:03:16.244
[Whirring Continues]

57
00:03:18.115 --> 00:03:19.781
[Whirring Stops]

58
00:03:21.000 --> 00:03:27.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

59
00:03:30.994 --> 00:03:33.879
Did you see it? Nothing. I
just think that you heard...

60
00:03:33.948 --> 00:03:37.181
[Loud Banging] Oh.
my God. Oh. my God!

61
00:03:37.250 --> 00:03:40.410
Go to Captain Redfern! Tell
him to warn the landing crew!

62
00:03:40.470 --> 00:03:43.721
And get emergency services!
There's someone down there!

63
00:03:43.790 --> 00:03:45.757
[Shrieking] It's gonna give!

64
00:03:45.825 --> 00:03:48.593
- It's gonna give!
- [Shrieking Continues]

65
00:03:48.661 --> 00:03:50.262
[Bolts Popping]

66
00:03:53.984 --> 00:03:56.000
[Screaming]

67
00:03:58.522 --> 00:04:02.608
Bravo Delta 347. you're
clear for Taxiway Foxtrot.

68
00:04:02.676 --> 00:04:06.177
Bravo Delta 347. clear
for Taxiway Foxtrot.

69
00:04:09.516 --> 00:04:13.551
Regis Air 753. this
is Kennedy Ground.

70
00:04:15.756 --> 00:04:17.922
Regis Air 753. Kennedy Ground.

71
00:04:19.410 --> 00:04:22.210
Regis 753. Kennedy Ground. Over.

72
00:04:23.213 --> 00:04:24.962
<i>[Beeping]</i>

73
00:04:25.031 --> 00:04:26.781
What the...

74
00:04:28.535 --> 00:04:29.934
Bishop!

75
00:04:30.003 --> 00:04:32.715
A Regis Air flight out of
Berlin... a 767 wide-body...

76
00:04:32.739 --> 00:04:34.906
Stopped on the service apron!

77
00:04:34.974 --> 00:04:37.442
What's it doing there? Apron's
dead. That's a blind spot.

78
00:04:37.511 --> 00:04:40.412
The plane just went dark.
Just shut down. Flat-out quit.

79
00:04:40.480 --> 00:04:42.931
No lights. no radio. no nothing.

80
00:04:43.000 --> 00:04:45.283
Regis 753. Kennedy Ground. Over.

81
00:04:45.352 --> 00:04:48.436
Regis 753. Kennedy
Ground. Please respond. Over.

82
00:04:50.190 --> 00:04:54.659
Okay. Shut down Foxtrot. Clear
all the gates and advise reroute.

83
00:04:54.728 --> 00:04:57.307
How many aboard?
Almost full flight. sir.

84
00:04:57.331 --> 00:05:01.265
Uh. passengers and crew.
about 210 souls. Holy Jesus.

85
00:05:01.335 --> 00:05:04.135
Shouldn't we wait for
first responders. sir?

86
00:05:16.450 --> 00:05:18.016
Bishop!

87
00:05:20.053 --> 00:05:21.386
Bishop. wait!

88
00:05:21.454 --> 00:05:23.454
Engines are shut down.

89
00:05:24.691 --> 00:05:26.290
No lights.

90
00:05:32.599 --> 00:05:35.099
Whoa. It's cold.

91
00:05:37.404 --> 00:05:39.404
It's like a dead animal.

92
00:05:41.875 --> 00:05:43.853
There's something
really wrong here.

93
00:05:43.877 --> 00:05:45.977
[Sirens Wailing]

94
00:05:46.046 --> 00:05:47.979
It's like it never moved.

95
00:05:48.048 --> 00:05:51.115
This looks so much bigger from
the ground than on the screen.

96
00:05:51.184 --> 00:05:54.185
I mean. they're like
buildings with wings.

97
00:05:56.557 --> 00:05:59.724
All the window shades
are shut. You see that?

98
00:05:59.793 --> 00:06:01.704
[Officer] Bishop!

99
00:06:01.728 --> 00:06:04.663
Hey. fellas. Bishop.

100
00:06:04.731 --> 00:06:06.431
Not all of 'em.

101
00:06:16.443 --> 00:06:19.444
Scramble all emergency
vehicles to Taxiway Foxtrot.

102
00:06:19.513 --> 00:06:21.057
SWAT? Homeland Security?

103
00:06:21.081 --> 00:06:23.615
Port Authority. FBI. TSA. CDC.

104
00:06:23.684 --> 00:06:26.384
Robbie. no one on
the tower calls home.

105
00:06:26.453 --> 00:06:28.220
No one shares the news.

106
00:06:28.288 --> 00:06:31.289
This is bad. Real bad.

107
00:06:32.191 --> 00:06:34.709
We got ourselves
a dead airplane.

108
00:06:52.846 --> 00:06:54.596
[Horns Honking]

109
00:07:14.918 --> 00:07:17.351
Hey. buddy. you can't park
there. There's a fire hydrant.

110
00:07:17.420 --> 00:07:19.988
It's a medical
emergency. Oh. is it really?

111
00:07:20.057 --> 00:07:23.102
Well. it will be if I can't
get this tie on right.

112
00:07:23.126 --> 00:07:26.560
- You know how to tie this?
- I don't know. man. I wear a clip-on.

113
00:07:26.629 --> 00:07:28.607
You're on your own. You
waiting for somebody?

114
00:07:28.631 --> 00:07:30.609
Yeah. Why? Here's
what I need you to do.

115
00:07:30.633 --> 00:07:34.769
The meter maid comes by. you tell
him it's official CDC business. Okay?

116
00:07:34.837 --> 00:07:36.837
Yeah. sure thing. [Door Closes]

117
00:07:38.992 --> 00:07:40.926
Zack.

118
00:07:40.994 --> 00:07:42.493
Hey. man.

119
00:07:42.562 --> 00:07:45.980
<i>♪♪ [Earphones: Rock]</i>

120
00:07:48.385 --> 00:07:50.180
Hey. dude. You're late.

121
00:07:50.204 --> 00:07:52.298
Five minutes. It can't
be helped. Ten. Dad.

122
00:07:52.322 --> 00:07:54.400
Ten? Okay. This is wrong.

123
00:07:54.424 --> 00:07:56.107
Maybe... Maybe 10.

124
00:07:57.127 --> 00:08:00.295
Well. I got a good
feeling about this.

125
00:08:00.363 --> 00:08:02.063
Wish us luck.

126
00:08:02.132 --> 00:08:03.932
[Kissing]

127
00:08:04.000 --> 00:08:05.566
Good luck.

128
00:08:11.241 --> 00:08:13.675
Five minutes. I know.
I know. I'm sorry.

129
00:08:13.744 --> 00:08:15.377
Ten.

130
00:08:15.445 --> 00:08:16.811
I... I texted you.

131
00:08:16.880 --> 00:08:18.546
Mmm. Five times.

132
00:08:18.615 --> 00:08:21.360
I wouldn't have gotten that 'cause I
don't text when I drive. It's not safe.

133
00:08:21.384 --> 00:08:22.828
Dr. Goodweather.
I... Eph. Please.

134
00:08:22.852 --> 00:08:24.953
She gets "Kelly."
my son gets "Zack."

135
00:08:25.022 --> 00:08:27.338
so Ephraim. or Eph. please.

136
00:08:28.825 --> 00:08:31.359
Dr. Goodweather.
this is the last of six...

137
00:08:31.428 --> 00:08:33.894
court-appointed custody
counseling sessions.

138
00:08:33.964 --> 00:08:35.847
You've been late
for four of them.

139
00:08:35.916 --> 00:08:37.448
You're gonna say that
I'm late because I don't

140
00:08:37.472 --> 00:08:38.995
want to be here. You
might be onto something.

141
00:08:39.019 --> 00:08:40.585
But I have a good reason.

142
00:08:40.654 --> 00:08:43.333
There was this outbreak of hantavirus
in this Alphabet City preschool.

143
00:08:43.357 --> 00:08:45.823
which is extremely rare
this far north and east...

144
00:08:45.893 --> 00:08:48.387
Dr. Goodweather. every time you
come in. you take over the session.

145
00:08:48.411 --> 00:08:50.389
Because I have
control issues. I know.

146
00:08:50.413 --> 00:08:52.396
But I have to
defend myself here...

147
00:08:52.465 --> 00:08:56.251
because this might
be my last chance.

148
00:08:57.670 --> 00:08:59.771
And I've thought long
and hard about this.

149
00:08:59.839 --> 00:09:03.992
It seems like you two have created
this narrative wherein I'm the bad guy.

150
00:09:04.060 --> 00:09:05.443
But why?

151
00:09:05.511 --> 00:09:09.114
Because I don't want
out of my marriage.

152
00:09:09.182 --> 00:09:11.999
'Cause I want things
back the way they were.

153
00:09:13.069 --> 00:09:15.131
But this isn't just
about you. Eph.

154
00:09:15.155 --> 00:09:18.405
What you want. Not anymore.

155
00:09:18.474 --> 00:09:21.275
[Phone Buzzing]

156
00:09:29.702 --> 00:09:31.202
I'm an epidemiologist.

157
00:09:31.271 --> 00:09:35.273
If I take time off. if I go
fly-fishing. people die.

158
00:09:35.341 --> 00:09:38.726
I get that you have an important
job. Ephraim. You're great at your job.

159
00:09:38.795 --> 00:09:41.006
You get straight
A's at your job.

160
00:09:41.030 --> 00:09:43.982
But I'm flunking our
marriage. Is that it?

161
00:09:44.050 --> 00:09:46.300
What are you writing?
Please stop writing.

162
00:09:48.488 --> 00:09:50.038
How horrible am I?

163
00:09:50.106 --> 00:09:52.073
You're not horrible.

164
00:09:53.543 --> 00:09:55.863
You're just barely present.

165
00:09:57.413 --> 00:10:02.133
I've done everything you've asked me
to in order to get us back together again.

166
00:10:02.202 --> 00:10:03.951
I quit drinking.

167
00:10:04.020 --> 00:10:08.122
You wanted time alone so I
moved out. against my own wishes.

168
00:10:08.191 --> 00:10:10.407
I've jumped through every
hoop. Tell me what you need.

169
00:10:10.476 --> 00:10:12.805
Our time apart has only
clarified things for me.

170
00:10:12.829 --> 00:10:14.824
It's allowed me to make
room in my life for Matt.

171
00:10:14.848 --> 00:10:17.343
We're going to be living
together now. and... Matt?

172
00:10:17.367 --> 00:10:19.517
The Sears guy you
were talking about?

173
00:10:19.586 --> 00:10:21.835
My house? Matt is a
operational manager.

174
00:10:21.904 --> 00:10:25.506
At Sears. Yeah. and he
gets straight A's at his job too.

175
00:10:25.575 --> 00:10:27.720
But at home he's present.

176
00:10:27.744 --> 00:10:29.855
Unlike you. he's...
He's always here.

177
00:10:29.879 --> 00:10:31.629
For both of us.

178
00:10:33.767 --> 00:10:36.600
Does he drive a green Prius?

179
00:10:36.669 --> 00:10:39.003
[Phone Buzzing]

180
00:10:43.009 --> 00:10:44.942
You want me to quit my job?

181
00:10:45.011 --> 00:10:46.944
I'll do it. I'll quit my job.

182
00:10:47.013 --> 00:10:49.492
I don't want you to quit
for me. I wouldn't be.

183
00:10:49.516 --> 00:10:51.148
I'd be quitting <i>because</i>
of you. for Zack.

184
00:10:51.217 --> 00:10:54.385
so he isn't driving around
Queens in a green goddamn Prius.

185
00:10:54.454 --> 00:10:56.871
- Dr. Goodweather.
- It's too late. Eph.

186
00:10:56.940 --> 00:10:58.823
I love you. but...

187
00:10:58.892 --> 00:11:01.893
How can you love
me and it be too late?

188
00:11:01.961 --> 00:11:04.328
You want a guy who's
crazy about Zack?

189
00:11:04.397 --> 00:11:06.147
Check.

190
00:11:06.215 --> 00:11:09.366
A guy who's crazy
about you? Check.

191
00:11:10.103 --> 00:11:12.570
Decent? Employed?

192
00:11:12.639 --> 00:11:15.456
Check. Check. [Phone Buzzing]

193
00:11:18.762 --> 00:11:20.712
[Buzzing Continues]

194
00:11:20.780 --> 00:11:23.881
[Beeping]

195
00:11:23.950 --> 00:11:26.634
- [Buzzing Continues]
- [Beeping Continues]

196
00:11:26.703 --> 00:11:28.987
Can't you see that this
is the problem. Eph?

197
00:11:29.056 --> 00:11:30.896
[Beeping Continues]
[Buzzing Continues]

198
00:11:30.940 --> 00:11:32.590
This is who you are.

199
00:11:36.012 --> 00:11:37.578
Go.

200
00:11:43.153 --> 00:11:46.454
[Buzzing Continues]
[Beeping Continues]

201
00:11:50.977 --> 00:11:53.594
Nora. how bad is it? <i>It's crazy.</i>

202
00:11:53.663 --> 00:11:56.180
I have. like. 12 different
agency officials...

203
00:11:56.249 --> 00:11:58.182
about to have a
dick-measuring contest here.

204
00:11:58.251 --> 00:12:00.952
No. it's an international
flight docking out of Berlin.

205
00:12:01.020 --> 00:12:04.705
The CDC gets the first call.
I can be there in 20 minutes.

206
00:12:04.774 --> 00:12:06.786
Can you keep the measuring
contest going that long?

207
00:12:06.810 --> 00:12:09.126
Don't worry. I'll
show them mine.

208
00:12:09.996 --> 00:12:11.596
Might just work.

209
00:12:14.201 --> 00:12:15.683
Sorry.

210
00:12:15.752 --> 00:12:19.687
I guess the meter reader didn't
see it as much of an emergency.

211
00:12:21.991 --> 00:12:23.691
Matt. huh?

212
00:12:23.759 --> 00:12:25.276
Yeah. that's me.

213
00:12:25.345 --> 00:12:26.911
Interesting.

214
00:12:26.979 --> 00:12:30.031
You know. it's too bad
I'm in such a rush. Matt.

215
00:12:30.099 --> 00:12:32.766
But I'm sure I'll see
you again at<i> my</i> house.

216
00:12:34.670 --> 00:12:36.770
You drive safe now. you hear?

217
00:12:45.715 --> 00:12:47.282
Hey. boss.

218
00:12:47.350 --> 00:12:49.784
Got my milk? Uh. yeah. here.

219
00:12:49.852 --> 00:12:53.521
Homeland Security is just desperate
to push the button on a terror alert.

220
00:12:53.590 --> 00:12:56.057
They're ready to get
on that plane right now.

221
00:12:56.125 --> 00:12:59.694
Jim. terrorists usually crash planes.
not land them and shut 'em down.

222
00:12:59.762 --> 00:13:02.175
What are the 911 calls
saying? There haven't been any.

223
00:13:02.199 --> 00:13:04.043
None? Uh-uh. Oh. shit.

224
00:13:04.067 --> 00:13:05.711
Dr. Goodweather.
Dr. Goodweather.

225
00:13:05.735 --> 00:13:08.514
When we flew to Chicago last week.
we sat on the tarmac for half an hour.

226
00:13:08.538 --> 00:13:10.616
people were freaking
out. texting. calling.

227
00:13:10.640 --> 00:13:14.658
There have been 200 people sitting
there silently for... Over an hour now.

228
00:13:14.727 --> 00:13:16.161
Pilots?

229
00:13:16.229 --> 00:13:17.796
Absolutely no movement.

230
00:13:17.864 --> 00:13:20.225
Have you done heat readings?
Surface of the plane is too cold.

231
00:13:20.249 --> 00:13:22.244
Blocks it all like a screen.

232
00:13:22.268 --> 00:13:25.815
We got Delsar mikes attached to the surface
of the plane. Picked up mostly silence.

233
00:13:25.839 --> 00:13:29.185
Mostly? Well. cooling pings
from the sheet metal contracting.

234
00:13:29.209 --> 00:13:31.490
Oh. and there's. uh. this.

235
00:13:36.799 --> 00:13:40.234
[Beeping] <i>[Whooshing. Static]</i>

236
00:13:40.303 --> 00:13:43.604
<i>[Thumping]</i>

237
00:13:43.672 --> 00:13:46.507
What do you think that
is? Rustling of some sort.

238
00:13:46.575 --> 00:13:49.877
Our experts think it's the engines
shutting down or liquid settling.

239
00:13:49.946 --> 00:13:52.174
- How long between
landing and shutdown?
- Six minutes.

240
00:13:52.198 --> 00:13:54.159
It's too short a window
for a contagious event.

241
00:13:54.183 --> 00:13:57.719
so I think CDC should
take a back seat on this one.

242
00:13:57.787 --> 00:13:59.086
I agree. Do you?

243
00:13:59.155 --> 00:14:01.322
Absolutely I do.

244
00:14:01.391 --> 00:14:03.402
How often do you
touch your face? What?

245
00:14:03.426 --> 00:14:07.511
In a day. How often? I
don't know. Once an hour?

246
00:14:07.580 --> 00:14:10.260
Every three minutes. You have
mouth-hand contact every five minutes.

247
00:14:10.299 --> 00:14:13.684
You touch somebody else every 20
minutes. That's how contagion works.

248
00:14:13.753 --> 00:14:16.521
You don't like terrorists?
Try negotiating with a virus.

249
00:14:16.590 --> 00:14:20.324
A virus exists only to find
a carrier and reproduce.

250
00:14:20.393 --> 00:14:22.860
That's all it does.
and it does it quickly.

251
00:14:22.929 --> 00:14:25.280
It has no political
views. it has no religious

252
00:14:25.304 --> 00:14:27.214
beliefs. it has no
cultural hang-ups.

253
00:14:27.283 --> 00:14:29.233
and it has no
respect for a badge.

254
00:14:29.302 --> 00:14:32.736
It has no concept
of time or geography.

255
00:14:32.805 --> 00:14:34.738
It might as well be
the Middle Ages...

256
00:14:34.807 --> 00:14:38.076
except for the convenience of
hitching a ride on a metal tube...

257
00:14:38.144 --> 00:14:40.027
flying from meal
to meal to meal.

258
00:14:41.130 --> 00:14:42.596
That's how a plague begins.

259
00:14:44.350 --> 00:14:48.102
So you still want to be the
first one through the door?

260
00:15:06.005 --> 00:15:08.756
<i>♪♪ [TV: Cartoon]</i>

261
00:15:08.825 --> 00:15:11.759
<i>[TV: Man] What do you want
us for? We ain't got nothin'.</i>

262
00:15:11.828 --> 00:15:13.528
[Dinging]

263
00:15:13.596 --> 00:15:16.575
So we heard you buy silver
without a receipt. man. Is that right?

264
00:15:16.599 --> 00:15:19.534
[Dinging]

265
00:15:21.437 --> 00:15:25.790
I'm always in need
of good silver. yes.

266
00:15:25.858 --> 00:15:31.562
Okay. well. uh. can I
get. uh. 50... for this?

267
00:15:34.517 --> 00:15:38.185
It's a very nice
timepiece indeed.

268
00:15:39.255 --> 00:15:41.655
I see that the band
links have snapped.

269
00:15:41.724 --> 00:15:45.509
You must have been
in a hurry taking it off.

270
00:15:45.578 --> 00:15:48.162
Can I. uh... Can
I get 50 for it?

271
00:15:48.230 --> 00:15:51.281
I can offer you maybe... 25.

272
00:15:52.535 --> 00:15:54.513
If the test is good.

273
00:15:54.537 --> 00:15:56.938
<i>♪♪ [Continues]</i>

274
00:15:57.006 --> 00:16:02.242
Unfortunately. this is
merely silver-plated brass.

275
00:16:02.311 --> 00:16:05.363
A cheap Eastern
European knockoff.

276
00:16:06.666 --> 00:16:07.948
[Groans]

277
00:16:08.017 --> 00:16:09.750
Listen very carefully. son.

278
00:16:09.819 --> 00:16:13.187
I know your little friend has a gun and
the hammer is cocked. but I don't care.

279
00:16:13.255 --> 00:16:16.940
I can control your entire body
weight from this pressure point.

280
00:16:17.009 --> 00:16:19.927
And this knife is pointing
straight at your radial artery.

281
00:16:19.995 --> 00:16:22.162
By the time he
clears his coat pocket.

282
00:16:22.231 --> 00:16:26.266
your artery will be punctured and
sliced wide open from top to bottom.

283
00:16:26.335 --> 00:16:29.036
You fall down bleeding.
I go under the counter...

284
00:16:29.105 --> 00:16:31.538
and your friend starts
shooting at an empty space.

285
00:16:31.608 --> 00:16:33.693
I can guarantee you
this... you will bleed

286
00:16:33.717 --> 00:16:36.026
out before the 911
operator answers the phone.

287
00:16:36.095 --> 00:16:37.828
That is option one.

288
00:16:37.897 --> 00:16:42.466
Option two is you release the
bills. your friend gives me the gun.

289
00:16:42.535 --> 00:16:46.304
he can keep the bullets... I don't
care... and you leave this store.

290
00:16:46.372 --> 00:16:50.457
Now. son. you have a choice.

291
00:16:50.526 --> 00:16:52.093
[Grunts]

292
00:17:02.705 --> 00:17:05.573
[Whimpering]

293
00:17:07.727 --> 00:17:10.645
Is there anything else I can do
for you gentlemen this evening?

294
00:17:15.835 --> 00:17:18.681
<i>[TV: Man] were
among those killed.</i>

295
00:17:18.705 --> 00:17:20.816
<i>Investigators are trying to
determine what sparked the fire.</i>

296
00:17:20.840 --> 00:17:23.808
<i>but they do not believe
it was suspicious.</i>

297
00:17:23.877 --> 00:17:25.376
<i>We have more now...</i>

298
00:17:25.445 --> 00:17:27.912
<i>on the developing story
out of JFK Airport tonight.</i>

299
00:17:27.980 --> 00:17:30.080
<i>You're looking at live
video of the airplane...</i>

300
00:17:30.149 --> 00:17:33.518
<i>identified as a Regis
Air wide-body jet.</i>

301
00:17:33.586 --> 00:17:35.068
<i>It originated in Berlin...</i>

302
00:17:35.137 --> 00:17:38.089
<i>and it shut down just
moments after landing.</i>

303
00:17:38.157 --> 00:17:41.192
<i>We are told there has been
no communication from the pilot.</i>

304
00:17:41.260 --> 00:17:43.455
<i>All attempts to contact
the flight crew...</i> Berlin.

305
00:17:43.479 --> 00:17:45.430
<i>Inside the aircraft
have been unsuccessful.</i>

306
00:17:45.498 --> 00:17:47.831
<i>Federal and local
agencies are on the scene.</i>

307
00:17:47.900 --> 00:17:50.234
<i>including officials from
the Port Authority...</i>

308
00:18:02.598 --> 00:18:06.133
<i>[Speakers: Irish Tenor]
♪ I wandered today ♪</i>

309
00:18:06.202 --> 00:18:09.836
<i>♪ To the hills. Maggie ♪</i>

310
00:18:09.905 --> 00:18:15.709
<i>♪ To watch the scene below ♪</i>

311
00:18:15.778 --> 00:18:17.912
<i>♪ The creek ♪</i>

312
00:18:17.980 --> 00:18:22.416
<i>♪ And the creaking
old mill. Maggie ♪</i>

313
00:18:22.484 --> 00:18:29.356
<i>♪ As we used to long ago ♪</i>

314
00:18:29.425 --> 00:18:32.492
<i>♪ The green grove is gone ♪</i>

315
00:18:32.562 --> 00:18:35.829
<i>♪ From the hills. Maggie ♪</i>

316
00:18:35.898 --> 00:18:41.035
<i>♪ Where first the daisies ♪</i>

317
00:18:41.103 --> 00:18:43.737
<i>♪ Sprung ♪</i>

318
00:18:43.806 --> 00:18:47.340
<i>♪ The creaking old mill ♪</i>

319
00:18:47.409 --> 00:18:51.712
<i>♪ Is still. Maggie ♪</i>

320
00:18:51.781 --> 00:18:55.149
<i>♪ Since you and I ♪</i>

321
00:18:55.218 --> 00:18:59.353
<i>♪ Were young ♪</i>

322
00:18:59.421 --> 00:19:02.189
<i>♪♪ [Continues]</i>

323
00:19:03.075 --> 00:19:04.842
He's back.

324
00:19:10.783 --> 00:19:12.265
I. uh...

325
00:19:13.803 --> 00:19:17.237
I don't know if I have the
strength to do it all over again.

326
00:19:25.147 --> 00:19:26.647
This time...

327
00:19:27.884 --> 00:19:29.550
I cannot fail.

328
00:19:38.193 --> 00:19:40.227
Feeling hungry?

329
00:19:51.457 --> 00:19:55.593
<i>♪♪ [Continues]</i>

330
00:20:17.383 --> 00:20:19.149
Enjoy. dear.

331
00:20:19.218 --> 00:20:22.954
[Heartbeat]

332
00:20:23.656 --> 00:20:28.125
<i>♪ When you and I ♪</i>

333
00:20:28.194 --> 00:20:30.294
<i>♪ Were ♪</i>

334
00:20:30.362 --> 00:20:32.696
<i>♪ Young ♪♪</i>

335
00:20:36.969 --> 00:20:39.953
[Sirens Wailing]

336
00:20:45.628 --> 00:20:48.962
I'm not looking forward
to what we'll see out there.

337
00:20:50.650 --> 00:20:52.450
You with me?

338
00:20:52.518 --> 00:20:55.218
Mysterious dead plane on
the tarmac not exciting enough?

339
00:20:55.287 --> 00:20:56.670
Sorry.

340
00:20:56.739 --> 00:20:59.005
It's just another...

341
00:20:59.074 --> 00:21:03.176
court-mandated happy
family therapy day.

342
00:21:03.245 --> 00:21:05.278
I noticed. You cut your hair.

343
00:21:05.348 --> 00:21:06.797
You cleaned up nicely.

344
00:21:06.866 --> 00:21:10.985
- Did you break out a tie?
- It's in my jacket pocket.

345
00:21:11.787 --> 00:21:13.687
Did it help? Uh. no.

346
00:21:13.756 --> 00:21:16.876
In fact. it didn't. She wants
to take Zack away from me.

347
00:21:16.943 --> 00:21:19.410
And there's a... man-child...

348
00:21:19.478 --> 00:21:21.661
living in my house with my son.

349
00:21:21.730 --> 00:21:23.314
Careful.

350
00:21:26.084 --> 00:21:27.652
Stay focused.

351
00:21:31.824 --> 00:21:35.075
You and Kelly have been
separated for a year. Things happen.

352
00:21:35.144 --> 00:21:37.745
It happened to us.
Oh. that's different.

353
00:21:37.814 --> 00:21:39.374
How is it different? It just is.

354
00:21:39.398 --> 00:21:41.732
I don't think Kelly would agree.

355
00:21:41.801 --> 00:21:44.669
She doesn't know. I
never told her. You didn't?

356
00:21:44.737 --> 00:21:46.282
No. She. uh...

357
00:21:46.306 --> 00:21:49.522
She filed. so I didn't tell
her. She doesn't know.

358
00:21:50.993 --> 00:21:53.860
You really know nothing
about women. do you?

359
00:21:54.914 --> 00:21:57.914
[Chattering]

360
00:22:04.407 --> 00:22:06.524
[Machine Powering Up]

361
00:22:06.592 --> 00:22:08.526
[Beeping]

362
00:22:08.594 --> 00:22:11.128
Okay. boss.

363
00:22:11.197 --> 00:22:13.637
Ready to go through the
looking glass? <i>Ready. Jim.</i>

364
00:22:15.234 --> 00:22:17.350
I got your milk.

365
00:22:18.354 --> 00:22:20.554
Keep it cold till I come back.

366
00:22:55.457 --> 00:22:57.408
Oh. my God.

367
00:22:57.476 --> 00:23:00.194
Jim. do you see this?

368
00:23:00.262 --> 00:23:03.130
<i>It's every passenger.
everyone on the plane.</i>

369
00:23:03.199 --> 00:23:05.882
Yeah. we're seeing it.

370
00:23:05.951 --> 00:23:08.234
<i>[Ephraim] They're all dead.</i>

371
00:23:08.303 --> 00:23:10.554
<i>[Jim] What is it. Eph?
What killed them?</i>

372
00:23:10.623 --> 00:23:12.222
No signs of struggle.

373
00:23:12.291 --> 00:23:15.559
[Nora] No signs of
blistering or chemical agents.

374
00:23:15.628 --> 00:23:17.160
No bruising.

375
00:23:20.299 --> 00:23:22.533
<i>[Ephraim] Faint discoloration.</i>

376
00:23:24.437 --> 00:23:25.919
<i>No markings.</i>

377
00:23:25.988 --> 00:23:28.705
Shit. What is it?

378
00:23:30.526 --> 00:23:31.926
Something sudden.

379
00:23:31.994 --> 00:23:33.527
Painless.

380
00:23:38.083 --> 00:23:41.551
All the window shades are
closed except for this one.

381
00:23:43.856 --> 00:23:46.106
<i>[Jim] Is it a gas
leak? Is it chemical?</i>

382
00:23:46.175 --> 00:23:48.456
<i>[Nora] The hazmat CAT's
picking up high levels of ammonia.</i>

383
00:23:48.510 --> 00:23:50.094
Nothing deadly though.

384
00:23:50.162 --> 00:23:52.207
There shouldn't be any
ammonia in the plane systems.

385
00:23:52.231 --> 00:23:54.414
- Jim. check the cargo manifest.
- Got it.

386
00:23:54.483 --> 00:23:56.783
I need a cargo manifest.
What about the Geiger?

387
00:23:56.852 --> 00:23:58.636
It's negative. Jim.

388
00:23:58.704 --> 00:24:02.389
<i>♪♪ [Pop. Faint]</i>

389
00:24:08.347 --> 00:24:11.331
<i>♪♪ [Earphones: Pop Continues]</i>

390
00:24:20.675 --> 00:24:24.094
No visible signs of trauma.

391
00:24:27.416 --> 00:24:28.916
<i>♪♪ [Off]</i>

392
00:24:35.057 --> 00:24:36.573
No bloating.

393
00:24:38.694 --> 00:24:41.929
The tongue and soft palate
appear pale. almost white.

394
00:24:49.388 --> 00:24:50.854
Eyes are clear.

395
00:24:52.424 --> 00:24:54.674
The skin is dry. It's inelastic.

396
00:24:54.743 --> 00:24:57.777
There's no frothing.
no nosebleeds.

397
00:24:58.614 --> 00:25:00.480
There's no signs of struggle.

398
00:25:01.883 --> 00:25:03.183
Almost peaceful.

399
00:25:07.807 --> 00:25:09.807
Let's try the UV lights.

400
00:25:20.152 --> 00:25:21.918
My God.

401
00:25:21.987 --> 00:25:23.887
What is this?

402
00:25:27.242 --> 00:25:29.225
<i>[Nora] Are you getting this?</i>

403
00:25:29.294 --> 00:25:32.929
<i>[Ephraim] These patterns are
everywhere. all over the cabin.</i>

404
00:25:34.099 --> 00:25:36.934
They're only visible
under UV light.

405
00:25:37.002 --> 00:25:39.436
[Nora] The pattern
is biological.

406
00:25:42.041 --> 00:25:44.641
Probably where the
ammonia is coming from.

407
00:25:45.761 --> 00:25:47.494
I'm taking samples.

408
00:25:48.647 --> 00:25:51.198
You take the front
galley. I'll take the rear.

409
00:26:42.834 --> 00:26:44.251
Jimbo.

410
00:26:44.319 --> 00:26:46.119
<i>[Ephraim] What is this?</i>

411
00:26:47.990 --> 00:26:49.923
No "Jimbo." please.

412
00:26:51.126 --> 00:26:53.944
Um. that's the
cargo compartment.

413
00:26:54.013 --> 00:26:57.064
Have it emptied. take
each piece of luggage...

414
00:26:57.132 --> 00:27:00.083
and check it for biological
agents and ammonia spectrum.

415
00:27:00.152 --> 00:27:01.618
<i>[Jim] Got it.</i>

416
00:27:32.101 --> 00:27:33.600
Jim?

417
00:27:33.669 --> 00:27:36.620
<i>[Nora] Cockpit door just opened.</i>

418
00:27:38.206 --> 00:27:39.706
<i>[Bishop] It should be locked.</i>

419
00:27:39.775 --> 00:27:42.242
<i>[Jim] Nora. that door's
not supposed to be open.</i>

420
00:27:42.311 --> 00:27:44.391
Just gonna take a quick look.

421
00:27:45.631 --> 00:27:49.366
Back out of there right now. Okay?
That door's supposed to be locked.

422
00:27:50.936 --> 00:27:53.236
<i>You shouldn't be in there alone.</i>

423
00:27:54.556 --> 00:27:56.690
Nora. can you hear me? Eph!

424
00:27:56.759 --> 00:28:00.010
<i>The door to the cockpit
is open. Nora is inside.</i>

425
00:28:05.167 --> 00:28:07.885
<i>[Jim] Nora? Eph?</i>

426
00:28:09.255 --> 00:28:11.488
<i>Come on. guys.
Somebody talk to me.</i>

427
00:28:13.058 --> 00:28:15.559
- [Gasps]
- [Gasping]

428
00:28:17.746 --> 00:28:19.429
Nora! I'm coming!

429
00:28:19.498 --> 00:28:21.147
[Loud Gasp]

430
00:28:21.216 --> 00:28:23.033
Help me.

431
00:28:23.102 --> 00:28:25.486
Lady. get the
light outta my face!

432
00:28:25.554 --> 00:28:27.754
[Gasping. Coughing]
<i>[Jim] I'm sending in SWAT!</i>

433
00:28:27.823 --> 00:28:30.051
No. Jim. Send paramedics.

434
00:28:30.075 --> 00:28:31.574
We've got survivors.

435
00:29:02.507 --> 00:29:04.007
[Bell Dings]

436
00:29:06.912 --> 00:29:09.112
Mr. Palmer. Shh.

437
00:29:09.181 --> 00:29:10.859
It's his dialysis session.

438
00:29:10.883 --> 00:29:12.449
He's asleep.

439
00:29:12.517 --> 00:29:14.751
Well. then wake him up.

440
00:29:14.820 --> 00:29:17.253
When he's ready. Now.

441
00:29:17.322 --> 00:29:19.690
In time. [Machine Beeps]

442
00:29:19.758 --> 00:29:21.692
<i>[Female Computer
Voice] Dialysis complete.</i>

443
00:29:21.760 --> 00:29:25.562
How long have you worked
for Stoneheart. Mr. Fitzwilliam?

444
00:29:26.565 --> 00:29:28.415
All my life. sir.

445
00:29:28.483 --> 00:29:32.185
Mr. Palmer aided me and my
brothers after my father passed.

446
00:29:32.254 --> 00:29:34.287
Gratitude.

447
00:29:34.356 --> 00:29:37.658
What an effective leash.

448
00:29:37.726 --> 00:29:40.093
[Palmer] Herr Eichhorst.

449
00:29:43.365 --> 00:29:45.599
Mr. Palmer.

450
00:29:45.668 --> 00:29:49.886
Herr Eichhorst is here
to pay his respects.

451
00:29:52.491 --> 00:29:54.651
I'll be outside if you need me.

452
00:29:57.062 --> 00:30:01.464
You may notice how chilly it
has gotten in here. Eichhorst.

453
00:30:01.533 --> 00:30:03.951
Twenty full degrees cooler
than the rest of the building.

454
00:30:04.019 --> 00:30:07.020
But not too cold
for you. I trust.

455
00:30:08.323 --> 00:30:09.590
Of course.

456
00:30:09.658 --> 00:30:12.275
It can't be too
cold for you. can it?

457
00:30:12.344 --> 00:30:14.422
The cargo has arrived safely.

458
00:30:14.446 --> 00:30:17.447
And all four survivors
have been found.

459
00:30:19.751 --> 00:30:21.451
Throughout my life.

460
00:30:21.520 --> 00:30:24.487
I've learned what it
feels to cross a line.

461
00:30:25.240 --> 00:30:26.690
to do things...

462
00:30:26.758 --> 00:30:29.592
Things that cannot be undone.

463
00:30:32.364 --> 00:30:34.731
That line...

464
00:30:34.800 --> 00:30:38.252
It has been crossed
now. hasn't it?

465
00:30:40.239 --> 00:30:42.105
Your breath.

466
00:30:42.174 --> 00:30:45.224
I'll never get used to... Yes.

467
00:30:45.293 --> 00:30:49.312
Even I miss breathing sometimes.

468
00:30:53.752 --> 00:30:55.451
Here we go.

469
00:30:56.655 --> 00:30:58.755
[Siren Blares]

470
00:31:00.526 --> 00:31:02.842
Wait for me. It won't be long.

471
00:31:09.884 --> 00:31:11.751
Everett.

472
00:31:11.820 --> 00:31:13.403
Eph.

473
00:31:14.390 --> 00:31:16.389
How bad is it?

474
00:31:20.545 --> 00:31:22.780
[Jim] The NTSB has
taken over a refrigerated

475
00:31:22.804 --> 00:31:24.447
chemical warehouse in the Bronx.

476
00:31:24.516 --> 00:31:27.767
They've turned it into a fully
contained mass casualty morgue.

477
00:31:27.836 --> 00:31:30.520
That's not necessary. Everett.
These bags are triple-sealed.

478
00:31:30.588 --> 00:31:32.956
I'm handing a dozen
bodies over to the CME.

479
00:31:33.025 --> 00:31:35.158
four from each section
of the plane. for autopsies.

480
00:31:35.227 --> 00:31:38.561
And the four survivors? I've secured
the isolation rooms at a local hospital.

481
00:31:38.630 --> 00:31:40.841
We need to move them
there right away. Of course.

482
00:31:40.865 --> 00:31:43.499
I'm sure they'll comply.
Comply? I'm not asking.

483
00:31:43.568 --> 00:31:46.169
I'm invoking the Health Powers
Act. Those four survivors stay.

484
