[Clamoring Continues]

729
00:47:46.914 --> 00:47:48.848
[Clamoring Quiets]

730
00:47:48.916 --> 00:47:51.550
[Camera Shutters Clicking]

731
00:47:51.619 --> 00:47:53.352
I'm Ephraim Goodweather.

732
00:47:53.420 --> 00:47:55.110
I'm the chief
medical officer for the

733
00:47:55.134 --> 00:47:57.173
Centers of Disease
Control here in New York.

734
00:47:57.242 --> 00:47:59.575
<i>I have been asked
to introduce myself...</i>

735
00:47:59.644 --> 00:48:03.779
<i>and to give you a preliminary update
about where we are in the investigation.</i>

736
00:48:03.848 --> 00:48:07.065
- [Clamoring Resumes]
- Please. If I could just...

737
00:48:09.153 --> 00:48:11.604
- Please. Please. Please.
- My son!

738
00:48:11.672 --> 00:48:13.338
[Clamoring Quiets]

739
00:48:17.411 --> 00:48:20.513
I think I'm supposed to stand
here and somehow reassure you.

740
00:48:22.383 --> 00:48:24.099
I can't do that.

741
00:48:27.171 --> 00:48:31.223
206 passengers on Regis
Air Flight 753 are dead.

742
00:48:31.291 --> 00:48:33.692
[All Gasping] And
we don't know why.

743
00:48:34.929 --> 00:48:37.863
Four passengers survived
and we don't know why.

744
00:48:37.931 --> 00:48:39.331
[Woman Sobbing]

745
00:48:39.400 --> 00:48:42.379
What I can tell you. having
been the first to board the plane.

746
00:48:42.403 --> 00:48:45.315
is that they all appeared to have
died peacefully. without distress.

747
00:48:45.339 --> 00:48:48.891
- That's the only comfort
I can give you at this time.
- [Sobbing Continues]

748
00:48:48.959 --> 00:48:51.327
You want answers...
Real answers...

749
00:48:51.396 --> 00:48:53.774
To what happened on
that plane. and so do I.

750
00:48:53.798 --> 00:48:55.914
And I won't quit until
we're all satisfied.

751
00:48:58.118 --> 00:48:59.796
<i>I don't care about
your promises!</i>

752
00:48:59.820 --> 00:49:03.339
I want my daughter back!
All you do is talk and talk!

753
00:49:03.407 --> 00:49:05.307
That's all you do!

754
00:49:07.678 --> 00:49:11.263
This is my daughter.
My daughter Emma.

755
00:49:11.331 --> 00:49:15.367
And I want to see her
again... Dead. alive.

756
00:49:15.436 --> 00:49:17.019
I'm her father!

757
00:49:17.088 --> 00:49:19.288
Don't you have
children of your own?

758
00:49:19.357 --> 00:49:21.339
Don't you have a heart?

759
00:49:31.051 --> 00:49:33.914
Forty-eight hours. I'll get you
answers. It's the best I can do.

760
00:49:33.938 --> 00:49:37.273
No. please! Please!
[All Shouting]

761
00:49:39.960 --> 00:49:42.093
Jesus. Goodweather. what
are you doing to me here?

762
00:49:42.162 --> 00:49:43.762
<i>Just tell me what you have.</i>

763
00:49:43.831 --> 00:49:46.711
I'm just getting into it now. I
haven't finished cutting all of them yet.

764
00:49:46.768 --> 00:49:51.003
- Just give me anything you can.
- <i>Okay. Top of the charts?</i>

765
00:49:51.072 --> 00:49:53.255
This here.

766
00:49:55.543 --> 00:49:57.175
Can you see this?

767
00:49:57.761 --> 00:49:59.361
<i>Here?</i>

768
00:49:59.430 --> 00:50:01.430
Yeah. What is that?

769
00:50:01.932 --> 00:50:03.732
It's an incision.

770
00:50:03.801 --> 00:50:07.653
Deep enough to puncture one wall of
the carotid artery without rupturing it.

771
00:50:07.722 --> 00:50:10.322
<i>Razor sharp. Clean cut.
No bruising. no trauma.</i>

772
00:50:10.390 --> 00:50:12.324
There's no instrument
that can do that.

773
00:50:12.392 --> 00:50:15.294
<i>Not that I'm aware of
anyway. Not with this precision.</i>

774
00:50:15.362 --> 00:50:17.879
Anything else? <i>Gets
way more interesting.</i>

775
00:50:17.948 --> 00:50:21.901
A spot-check of six other
corpses revealed the same thing.

776
00:50:21.969 --> 00:50:25.820
<i>The exact same wound
in the exact same place.</i>

777
00:50:25.889 --> 00:50:28.935
Are you telling me that the other
passengers have the same incision?

778
00:50:28.959 --> 00:50:30.208
<i>Or puncture. yes.</i>

779
00:50:30.277 --> 00:50:32.494
All the ones I've
looked at so far.

780
00:50:32.563 --> 00:50:35.931
There is one more
intriguing abnormality.

781
00:50:48.629 --> 00:50:51.146
I... I don't... What the
hell am I looking at?

782
00:50:51.215 --> 00:50:53.794
On our screen that
looks white. <i>Because it is.</i>

783
00:50:53.818 --> 00:50:55.350
<i>White and opalescent.</i>

784
00:50:55.419 --> 00:50:57.135
Blood proteins are separating?

785
00:50:57.204 --> 00:50:59.783
<i>No. in fact. there's a complete
absence of hypostasis.</i>

786
00:50:59.807 --> 00:51:01.507
<i>No blood pooling anywhere.</i>

787
00:51:01.576 --> 00:51:04.259
<i>And an absolute
absence of erythrocytes.</i>

788
00:51:04.328 --> 00:51:07.207
<i>I'll know more once I cut
into the liver and kidneys. but...</i>

789
00:51:07.231 --> 00:51:10.010
I'm sorry to do this to you. but you're
gonna have to do the preliminary alone.

790
00:51:10.034 --> 00:51:12.646
- I don't want any of this
leaking to the press.
- Okay. buddy.

791
00:51:12.670 --> 00:51:15.871
- But you'll owe me.
- For the rest of my life.

792
00:51:16.707 --> 00:51:18.123
Shit.

793
00:51:18.192 --> 00:51:20.672
<i>[Reporter] This just in. It appears
we now have confirmation...</i>

794
00:51:20.711 --> 00:51:23.378
Eph. I'm sorry. but I think you're
gonna want to talk to this man.

795
00:51:23.447 --> 00:51:26.365
<i>One of the four surviving
passengers is the goth rock star Bolivar.</i>

796
00:51:26.433 --> 00:51:28.633
<i>His followers are
up in arms as...</i>

797
00:51:28.702 --> 00:51:31.320
Dr. Goodweather. my
name is Abraham Setrakian.

798
00:51:31.389 --> 00:51:33.867
It's very nice to meet you.
I can't talk right now. Eph.

799
00:51:33.891 --> 00:51:36.658
He says he has some
insight into the outbreak here.

800
00:51:36.727 --> 00:51:39.689
Great. Mr. Kent here can
take down your information.

801
00:51:39.713 --> 00:51:42.447
Time is of the essence. Doctor.

802
00:51:42.516 --> 00:51:44.400
- It certainly is. Jim?
- Eph.

803
00:51:44.469 --> 00:51:48.337
You have to listen to me. I
have seen this disease before.

804
00:51:48.406 --> 00:51:51.740
I have faced it before.
Y-Y-You must contain it.

805
00:51:51.808 --> 00:51:53.408
You've seen it before? Where?

806
00:51:53.477 --> 00:51:55.489
I assure you. we're taking
every available precaution.

807
00:51:55.513 --> 00:51:58.630
You're not. You can't.
And he is counting on that.

808
00:52:00.067 --> 00:52:01.566
"He"?

809
00:52:02.736 --> 00:52:05.504
It is too much to
say all at once here...

810
00:52:05.573 --> 00:52:07.740
without... sounding crazy.

811
00:52:09.510 --> 00:52:10.943
No. of course not.

812
00:52:11.011 --> 00:52:12.989
Jim. we're going
to the cargo hold.

813
00:52:13.013 --> 00:52:15.491
Please take care of this
gentleman for me. Thank you.

814
00:52:15.515 --> 00:52:18.149
It's okay. Just come with me.

815
00:52:18.218 --> 00:52:22.521
The bodies. They are not
decomposing normally. yes?

816
00:52:22.590 --> 00:52:24.984
The tissues are still pliable.
How do you know that?

817
00:52:25.008 --> 00:52:26.675
Nora. Nora.

818
00:52:26.744 --> 00:52:28.643
Listen to me now.

819
00:52:28.712 --> 00:52:31.296
What I'm about to
say I do not say lightly.

820
00:52:31.365 --> 00:52:34.685
All the passengers on
that plane. dead and alive.

821
00:52:36.370 --> 00:52:37.636
they must be destroyed.

822
00:52:37.705 --> 00:52:39.638
[Bystanders Murmuring]
[Man] What was that?

823
00:52:39.706 --> 00:52:42.007
Destroyed? Okay.
Here you go. fellas.

824
00:52:42.076 --> 00:52:43.492
Feel better.

825
00:52:43.561 --> 00:52:48.614
The heads must be severed.
the bodies burned... destroyed!

826
00:52:51.802 --> 00:52:54.620
Doctor. did you find the coffin?

827
00:52:54.688 --> 00:52:57.767
If you have the coffin. then you
still have him. It is not too late!

828
00:52:57.791 --> 00:53:00.075
Destroy the coffin!

829
00:53:00.144 --> 00:53:03.128
Do not allow it
across the river!

830
00:53:14.791 --> 00:53:16.991
As advised by Dr. Goodweather.

831
00:53:17.060 --> 00:53:20.128
I will examine the
body under UV light.

832
00:53:46.841 --> 00:53:49.525
How did that old man
know about the coffin?

833
00:53:49.593 --> 00:53:51.226
You mean the cabinet?

834
00:53:51.295 --> 00:53:54.340
He called it a coffin. I
know what he called it.

835
00:53:54.364 --> 00:53:57.833
He also told us to
destroy 206 bodies.

836
00:53:57.902 --> 00:53:59.902
And he had a sword.

837
00:54:02.372 --> 00:54:04.039
Nora!

838
00:54:08.178 --> 00:54:10.379
What?

839
00:54:10.448 --> 00:54:12.781
What the hell is that?

840
00:54:18.222 --> 00:54:19.916
Looks like a horsehair worm.

841
00:54:19.940 --> 00:54:22.474
Or a<i> Dirofilaria immitis.</i>

842
00:54:23.443 --> 00:54:26.444
Body is simple.
It's just collagen.

843
00:54:26.513 --> 00:54:29.414
Degenerate non-functional
digestive system.

844
00:54:32.870 --> 00:54:34.903
Look at that. It's beautiful.

845
00:54:35.940 --> 00:54:38.323
It's looking for a
host. It's desperate.

846
00:54:51.005 --> 00:54:54.472
So. it's not airborne.

847
00:54:54.541 --> 00:54:56.124
That's the carrier.

848
00:55:03.984 --> 00:55:05.984
Eph. look.

849
00:55:16.764 --> 00:55:18.329
Soil.

850
00:55:35.765 --> 00:55:37.699
Hey! Where's that cabinet?

851
00:55:37.768 --> 00:55:40.018
What cabinet?

852
00:55:47.861 --> 00:55:50.412
There. Right there. Rewind.

853
00:55:50.481 --> 00:55:52.658
Can you go slower?
Frame by frame?

854
00:55:52.682 --> 00:55:55.384
There must be a gap or
a cut. No. there's no cut.

855
00:55:55.452 --> 00:55:57.285
Watch the time code.

856
00:56:00.907 --> 00:56:03.291
Wait. two seconds. Go back.

857
00:56:04.528 --> 00:56:06.573
[Ephraim] Start there.

858
00:56:06.597 --> 00:56:08.930
Wait. Wait. There!

859
00:56:12.002 --> 00:56:14.502
What's that distortion?

860
00:56:14.572 --> 00:56:16.170
[Man] I don't know.

861
00:56:16.239 --> 00:56:17.956
But it grabs the box...

862
00:56:18.025 --> 00:56:21.593
and lifts off... up.

863
00:56:23.647 --> 00:56:26.331
That box was 500 pounds.
Nothing can lift it up like that.

864
00:56:26.399 --> 00:56:29.839
The old man said. "If you have
the coffin. you still have him."

865
00:56:30.837 --> 00:56:32.621
Him.

866
00:56:36.910 --> 00:56:39.828
This footage is only
seven minutes old.

867
00:56:41.197 --> 00:56:43.717
The box is still in the airport.

868
00:57:15.649 --> 00:57:17.282
Mm-hmm.

869
00:57:28.328 --> 00:57:30.461
What the hell is that?

870
00:57:31.731 --> 00:57:33.432
Crazy-ass white boy.

871
00:57:44.211 --> 00:57:46.862
Come on. come on.
come on. Pick up.

872
00:57:46.930 --> 00:57:49.050
Jim. Where are you? Right now.

873
00:57:49.099 --> 00:57:51.416
At the main garage
door. funneling traffic out.

874
00:57:51.485 --> 00:57:53.462
Stop it! Stop everyone!
This is an emergency!

875
00:57:53.486 --> 00:57:55.932
You need to seal off the
perimeter of the airport.

876
00:57:55.956 --> 00:57:58.852
That box? Remember the
box with the markings on it?

877
00:57:58.876 --> 00:58:01.343
Yeah. yeah. The Berlin
cargo omit. <i>That's the one.</i>

878
00:58:01.411 --> 00:58:03.579
Now listen carefully. Jim.

879
00:58:03.647 --> 00:58:06.815
We need to stop all
vehicles big enough to hold it.

880
00:58:06.884 --> 00:58:09.317
No vans. no trucks. nothing.

881
00:58:09.386 --> 00:58:11.569
<i>No big vehicles. No exceptions.</i>

882
00:58:11.638 --> 00:58:14.572
Okay. no big vehicles in or
out of the security zone. Got it.

883
00:58:14.641 --> 00:58:16.474
All right. everybody. listen up.

884
00:58:16.543 --> 00:58:21.663
I want none of these trucks... big-sized
vehicles released without my authorization.

885
00:58:24.635 --> 00:58:26.684
Come on.

886
00:58:26.753 --> 00:58:28.487
Oh. yeah. Oh. yeah.

887
00:58:44.071 --> 00:58:46.537
Pull up there. sir.
I'll be right with you.

888
00:58:46.607 --> 00:58:48.190
Shit.

889
00:58:48.259 --> 00:58:49.925
Shit. shit. shit.

890
00:58:57.184 --> 00:58:59.318
[Chamber Clicks]

891
00:58:59.386 --> 00:59:01.853
ID and permit. Oh. yeah. man.

892
00:59:01.921 --> 00:59:04.055
Crazy what's happening. huh?

893
00:59:13.734 --> 00:59:15.929
What do you want
me to do with this?

894
00:59:15.953 --> 00:59:19.337
[Dog Barking]

895
00:59:22.943 --> 00:59:25.944
Step out of the vehicle.
Open the cargo area. sir.

896
00:59:26.013 --> 00:59:27.640
[Barking Continues]
Step out of the vehicle. sir.

897
00:59:27.664 --> 00:59:29.909
- Get that light out of my face.
- Step out of the vehicle. sir.

898
00:59:29.933 --> 00:59:31.600
Can I get my seat belt?

899
00:59:41.411 --> 00:59:43.027
Hey. What's going on here?

900
00:59:45.348 --> 00:59:47.849
I asked for ID. He gave me this.

901
00:59:53.590 --> 00:59:55.991
Well. this is one
of our vehicles.

902
00:59:56.059 --> 00:59:57.420
You can let him through. Sir?

903
00:59:57.444 --> 00:59:59.727
I said. let him through!

904
01:00:04.017 --> 01:00:06.535
You tell those sons
of bitches I'm done.

905
01:00:06.603 --> 01:00:09.704
I came through for them.
but now I am done. You got it?

906
01:00:15.629 --> 01:00:17.361
Okay. go.

907
01:00:19.332 --> 01:00:21.783
[Bone Saw Whirring]

908
01:00:21.852 --> 01:00:24.152
[Whirring Stops]

909
01:00:24.220 --> 01:00:27.155
I have now removed
the chest plate...

910
01:00:27.223 --> 01:00:29.925
of one of the subjects... <i>♪♪
[Speakers: Man Singing Pop]</i>

911
01:00:29.993 --> 01:00:32.727
and found...

912
01:00:32.796 --> 01:00:34.729
abnormal neoplasms...

913
01:00:34.798 --> 01:00:37.732
in the heart. liver...

914
01:00:40.136 --> 01:00:41.636
and kidneys.

915
01:00:41.705 --> 01:00:44.840
<i>♪♪ [Continues]</i>

916
01:00:44.908 --> 01:00:48.860
The growths do not seem
like oncological aberrations...

917
01:00:48.929 --> 01:00:51.513
but almost like...

918
01:00:51.581 --> 01:00:54.883
new. fully functional
organs. <i>♪ Touching me ♪</i>

919
01:00:54.951 --> 01:00:57.619
<i>♪ Touching you ♪</i>

920
01:00:57.687 --> 01:00:59.187
Hmm.

921
01:00:59.256 --> 01:01:02.357
<i>♪ Sweet Caroline ♪</i>

922
01:01:03.827 --> 01:01:08.179
<i>♪ Good times never
seemed so good ♪</i>

923
01:01:08.248 --> 01:01:10.248
[Clattering]

924
01:01:10.316 --> 01:01:13.317
<i>♪ I've been inclined ♪</i>

925
01:01:14.454 --> 01:01:18.573
<i>♪ To believe they never would ♪</i>

926
01:01:18.642 --> 01:01:21.410
<i>♪ But now I ♪</i>

927
01:01:22.413 --> 01:01:24.279
<i>♪ Look at the night ♪</i>

928
01:01:26.150 --> 01:01:28.316
<i>♪ And it don't seem so lonely ♪</i>

929
01:01:28.385 --> 01:01:30.185
[Metallic Squeak]

930
01:01:30.254 --> 01:01:33.805
<i>♪ We fill it up with only two ♪</i>

931
01:01:33.874 --> 01:01:36.408
[Squishing]

932
01:01:38.144 --> 01:01:40.161
<i>♪ And when I hurt ♪</i>

933
01:01:41.415 --> 01:01:44.516
<i>♪ Hurtin' runs off
my shoulders ♪</i>

934
01:01:44.584 --> 01:01:46.751
<i>♪ How can I hurt ♪</i>

935
01:01:46.819 --> 01:01:49.371
<i>♪ Holding you? ♪</i>

936
01:01:50.190 --> 01:01:51.623
What...

937
01:01:51.692 --> 01:01:53.424
<i>♪ Warm ♪</i>

938
01:01:53.493 --> 01:01:56.078
[Gasping]

939
01:01:56.146 --> 01:01:58.846
<i>♪ Touching warm ♪</i>

940
01:02:00.184 --> 01:02:02.617
<i>♪ Reaching out ♪</i>

941
01:02:03.519 --> 01:02:05.720
<i>♪ Touching me ♪</i>

942
01:02:05.789 --> 01:02:09.224
<i>♪ Touching you ♪</i>

943
01:02:10.910 --> 01:02:13.278
<i>♪ Sweet Caroline ♪</i>

944
01:02:13.347 --> 01:02:15.730
[Gasping]

945
01:02:15.799 --> 01:02:18.416
<i>♪ Good times never
seemed so good ♪</i>

946
01:02:18.485 --> 01:02:20.685
[Groaning]

947
01:02:21.788 --> 01:02:23.788
<i>♪ I've been inclined ♪</i>

948
01:02:26.310 --> 01:02:30.078
<i>♪ To believe they never would ♪</i>

949
01:02:30.147 --> 01:02:33.165
<i>♪ Oh. no. no ♪</i>

950
01:02:33.233 --> 01:02:35.616
[Corpses Groaning. Growling]

951
01:02:38.655 --> 01:02:41.907
[Corpses Snarling]

952
01:02:43.209 --> 01:02:45.526
No. N...

953
01:02:45.596 --> 01:02:47.462
[Screaming]

954
01:02:47.530 --> 01:02:49.430
<i>♪ Sweet Caroline ♪</i>

955
01:02:50.734 --> 01:02:54.803
<i>♪ Good times never
seemed so good ♪</i>

956
01:02:57.273 --> 01:02:59.975
<i>♪ Sweet Caroline ♪♪</i>

957
01:03:00.043 --> 01:03:01.609
[Siren Blares]

958
01:03:05.532 --> 01:03:08.065
Sorry. Eph. Nothing.

959
01:03:08.134 --> 01:03:09.801
You got anything here?

960
01:03:09.870 --> 01:03:13.637
Just trying to figure out how a
500-pound. nine-foot-tall coffin...

961
01:03:13.706 --> 01:03:15.390
got up and walked away.

962
01:03:17.194 --> 01:03:18.838
You called it a coffin.

963
01:03:18.862 --> 01:03:22.296
We'll get a break. We always do.
We just gotta find someplace to start.

964
01:03:26.352 --> 01:03:28.219
This is where we start.

965
01:03:28.288 --> 01:03:29.788
What the hell are those?

966
01:03:30.924 --> 01:03:32.424
Something new.

967
01:03:45.055 --> 01:03:48.589
S-E-T-R-A-K-I-A-N.

968
01:03:48.658 --> 01:03:50.792
Setrakian?

969
01:03:50.861 --> 01:03:52.427
What is that?

970
01:03:52.495 --> 01:03:53.761
Armenian.

971
01:03:53.831 --> 01:03:55.463
Is that where you're from?

972
01:03:55.532 --> 01:03:57.199
At one time.

973
01:03:59.169 --> 01:04:02.470
How soon may I leave? Well.
nothing happens till Monday.

974
01:04:02.539 --> 01:04:04.906
Then charges are filed.
But it's almost dawn now.

975
01:04:06.143 --> 01:04:08.376
Hey! Hey. cop! Come on. man!

976
01:04:08.445 --> 01:04:10.765
Quiet down in here!

977
01:04:14.017 --> 01:04:15.750
You a librarian?

978
01:04:18.021 --> 01:04:19.887
Oh.

979
01:04:19.956 --> 01:04:22.356
That's some ancient ink
you got there. old man.

980
01:04:22.425 --> 01:04:24.809
What is that? Numbers? Yeah.

981
01:04:24.878 --> 01:04:26.510
Numbers.

982
01:04:26.579 --> 01:04:29.180
Does it mean anything?

983
01:04:31.884 --> 01:04:33.884
Only to me.

984
01:04:43.046 --> 01:04:45.413
[Eichhorst] Everything
went as planned.

985
01:04:48.051 --> 01:04:50.985
Love is going to
guide them all back...

986
01:04:51.054 --> 01:04:53.154
to their homes.

987
01:04:53.222 --> 01:04:55.289
to their loved ones.

988
01:04:57.961 --> 01:05:00.494
Curious detail.

989
01:05:00.564 --> 01:05:04.899
An old man with a sword
was arrested at the airport.

990
01:05:07.537 --> 01:05:10.738
The Jew. He's still at it.

991
01:05:11.741 --> 01:05:13.340
After all these years.

992
01:05:13.409 --> 01:05:16.177
You must admire him for that.

993
01:05:16.245 --> 01:05:19.513
I'll take care of him. Mmm.

994
01:05:19.583 --> 01:05:21.849
I look out upon this island...

995
01:05:22.719 --> 01:05:25.086
and I savor what is to come...

996
01:05:26.422 --> 01:05:28.056
Purity.

997
01:05:28.124 --> 01:05:29.657
Mr. Fitzwilliam.

998
01:05:31.094 --> 01:05:35.697
A sentimental man would
venture out into the city tonight...

999
01:05:35.765 --> 01:05:38.967
to walk these
streets one last time...

1000
01:05:40.269 --> 01:05:42.770
before the fall.

1001
01:05:44.207 --> 01:05:47.041
Do you require
anything else. sir? No.

1002
01:05:47.110 --> 01:05:49.677
For the first time in my life.

1003
01:05:49.746 --> 01:05:52.246
I have everything I need.

1004
01:06:07.480 --> 01:06:11.148
<i>♪♪ [Speakers. Hip-hop:
Man Rapping In Spanish]</i>

1005
01:06:11.217 --> 01:06:13.734
<i>♪♪ [Continues]</i>
♪♪ [Humming Along]

1006
01:06:19.659 --> 01:06:22.159
[Ringing] <i>[TV: Man
Shouting In Spanish]</i>

1007
01:06:23.162 --> 01:06:24.202
Hello?

1008
01:06:24.264 --> 01:06:26.698
<i>- [Speaking Spanish]</i>
- [Spanish]

1009
01:06:26.766 --> 01:06:29.333
<i>It's Gusto.</i> ¿Quién más?

1010
01:06:29.402 --> 01:06:32.436
Huh? No.<i> mami.</i> no. I'm not
smoking. Are you kidding me?

1011
01:06:32.505 --> 01:06:35.640
I'm working. Just calling to
check in to see what you're up to.

1012
01:06:35.708 --> 01:06:38.877
<i>Is Crispin home?</i>
He is. [Spanish]

1013
01:06:41.414 --> 01:06:44.715
Mama. one beer left.
Why do you do this to me?

1014
01:06:44.784 --> 01:06:48.236
How many times do I gotta tell
you? I'm making his breakfast.

1015
01:06:48.304 --> 01:06:51.055
I'm getting on the bridge now.
I'll be home in an hour. <i>Okay.</i>

1016
01:06:55.061 --> 01:06:58.195
<i>♪♪ [Hip-hop Continues]</i>

1017
01:06:58.264 --> 01:07:00.248
I don't know what you are.

1018
01:07:00.317 --> 01:07:02.183
but you're bringing
me good luck.

1019
01:07:02.252 --> 01:07:05.253
<i>♪♪ [Continues]</i>
♪♪ [Singing Along]

1020
01:07:13.329 --> 01:07:15.497
<i>[Abraham Narrating]
Love. you see.</i>

1021
01:07:15.565 --> 01:07:19.634
<i>is the one force that
cannot be explained.</i>

1022
01:07:19.703 --> 01:07:23.238
<i>cannot be broken down
into a chemical process.</i>

1023
01:07:23.306 --> 01:07:27.075
<i>It is the beacon that
guides us back home...</i>

1024
01:07:27.143 --> 01:07:29.143
<i>when no one is there...</i>

1025
01:07:29.212 --> 01:07:32.580
<i>and the light that
illuminates our loss.</i>

1026
01:07:34.017 --> 01:07:37.018
<i>Its absence robs
us of all pleasure.</i>

1027
01:07:37.954 --> 01:07:40.821
<i>of our capacity for joy.</i>

1028
01:07:40.891 --> 01:07:43.358
<i>It makes our nights darker...</i>

1029
01:07:44.261 --> 01:07:46.394
<i>and our days gloomier.</i>

1030
01:07:53.870 --> 01:07:56.170
<i>But when we find love.</i>

1031
01:07:56.239 --> 01:07:58.339
<i>no matter how wrong.</i>

1032
01:07:58.408 --> 01:08:01.042
<i>how sad or how terrible.</i>

1033
01:08:01.111 --> 01:08:03.344
<i>we cling to it.</i>

1034
01:08:03.413 --> 01:08:05.846
<i>It gives us our strength.</i>

1035
01:08:05.916 --> 01:08:07.799
<i>It holds us upright.</i>

1036
01:08:09.920 --> 01:08:11.886
<i>It feeds on us...</i>

1037
01:08:11.955 --> 01:08:14.322
<i>and we feed on it.</i>

1038
01:08:43.136 --> 01:08:46.137
[Clock Chiming]

1039
01:08:47.573 --> 01:08:50.375
[Sobbing] Emma.

1040
01:08:50.443 --> 01:08:52.643
Emma. [Tapping]

1041
01:09:07.327 --> 01:09:09.193
[Speaking French]

1042
01:09:32.585 --> 01:09:34.785
[Sniffling] Emma.

1043
01:09:34.854 --> 01:09:36.587
[Sobbing] Oh. baby.

1044
01:09:54.657 --> 01:09:57.725
<i>[Abraham Narrating]
Love is our grace.</i>

1045
01:10:00.263 --> 01:10:01.529
<i>Love...</i>

1046
01:10:01.598 --> 01:10:03.598
<i>is our downfall.</i>

